==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cliff limestone
<hw>Cliff" lime"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>A
series of limestone strata found in Ohio and farther west, presenting
bluffs along the rivers and valleys, formerly supposed to be of one
formation, but now known to be partly Silurian and partly
Devonian.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cliffy</ent>⟦br⟧
